# Testing rules

- Before claiming done, prefer `pnpm test`, `pnpm -F @tell/schema build`, and `pnpm -F @tell/web typecheck`.
- Root TypeScript is strict with `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`; avoid unchecked array/object access.
- Vitest includes `packages/**/*.test.ts`; package tests should stay close to the package they verify.
- Detector changes require golden assertions against `fixtures/reports/capture.json`.
- Taste tests must mock model calls and validate zod/reflection fallback behavior.
- UI changes should preserve keyboard access, `focus-visible`, reduced motion, and non-color verdict encoding.
- Known lower-coverage areas: redesign diffs, seam drag math, and the monolithic web page. Add focused tests when touching them.
